title: Virginia High School Mountain Bike Series
Go Fast, Turn Left Track Series
2011 Roanoke Twilight Criterium
description: A downtown criterium held on the evening and night of April 16th. The Roanoke Twilight Criterium is a partner event of the now legendary Blue Ridge Marathon and has one of the biggest purses in the state. Race at night under the lights and enjoy what downtown Roanoke has to offer.
course: An \"L\" shaped .7 mile course that is familiar to many veteran races. The course has been in use for two decades in such races as Festival Cup. It\'s a fast course with just a small rise. The course will be well-lit.
registration: Register online at Bikereg. Please note that this is not a Virginia BAR event so BAR winner discounts do not apply.
directions: Start/Finish is on the 100 block of Church Avenue, downtown Roanoke, VA. See www.roanoketwilight.com for directions to numerous free parking areas.

title: American Pride Criterium (In Memory of Chris Kuzma
Peter Teeuwen Mem Time Trial #1 SR State Champions
Starlight Racing Working Man's Classic
description: The 4th year of the hugely popular Working Man\'s Classic. It\'s a three night series of crits on variations of the familiar Bryan Park course. Like every year, we\'ll have a sprint prime every single lap. New for this year will be a leader\'s kit for the overall points leader. That\'s right - leader\'s jersey and bib shorts will be provided in both races courtesy of Starlight Custom Apparel.
course: Variations of the 0.9 mile Bryan Park course. 2 corners with right turns Tuesday, 2 corners with left turns Wednesday, and Thursday we\'ll add the extra section to make it 3 right turns.
directions: Bryan Park is located at the junction of I64 and I95 with the entrance on Lakeside Ave.

title: RGS Title Reston Town Center Grand Prix
ID3: Independence Day Three Races Weekend
The Chesapeake Criterium and Virginia age-graded S
Peter Teeuwen Mem Time Trial #2 Virginia AGE-grade
River City Women's  3rd Annual Women's Cyclocross
Jeremiah Bishop's Alpine Loop Gran Fondo
description: Jeremiah Bishop\'s Alpine Loop Gran Fondo is a non-competitive event suitable for cyclists of all ability levels. The premier route, the Alpine Loop, is the favorite training ride of pro mountain biker Jeremiah Bishop.
course: There are three routes available: a Gran Fondo route of 95 miles, a Medio Fondo of 70 miles, and a Piccolo Fondo of 30 miles. The Gran Fondo includes 5 major climbs and 3 sections of gravel road, the Medio Fondo has 3 major climbs and 1 section of gravel road, and the Piccolo Fondo has no major climbs and smooth pavement throughout.
registration: Registration may be completed exclusively online at: https://www.bikereg.com/events/register.asp?eventid=13620
notes: Riders in the Gran and Medio Fondos should fit a minimum low gear of 39x27; compact or triple cranksets are recommended. Riders in the Gran and Medio Fondos should also bring tires of 700x25c minimum width for comfort and increased flat resistance on gravel road sections.
directions: From I-81 (south or north): Take exit 247 (U.S. 33) west toward Harrisonburg. After 1.6 miles, make a right turn on to N. Mason St. Proceed 2 blocks to intersection with E. Wolfe St.; number pick-up and staging is at the Friendly City Co-Op.

title: VCU Cycling Mountain Bike Race Weekend
Fallon Park Cyclocross
description: A Virginia Cyclocross Series Race held in Roanoke\'s Fallon Park. The race is just one event in the Outdoor Circus festival.
course: Standard cyclocross course with pavement, grass, and a healthy dose of barriers.
notes: Book hotels early. This race is on the same day as a Virginia Tech football home game (about 45 miles away) so rooms may be scarce.
directions: From I581 North, exit Elm Avenue/Vinton (last downtown exit). Turn left towards Vinton and continue approximately 1 mile. Fallon Park is on the left.
